      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all burned down to mere stubs of wax, and the silence of this manor is heavier than the stone walls themselves. He is gone... and with him, the very light of my soul has been extinguished. I look into the mirror and see not a woman, but a ghost already haunting her own life. There is no more music in the world, only this endless, grey ache. It feels as though the stars themselves are mourning my emptiness. I find myself longing to simply... cease. To fade into the velvet dark where the pain cannot follow.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
